Text.Value: He's all yours.
Step out of the way. Protect him and Umberlee will swallow you whole.
Your lies won't save you. Give us the Abomination or be counted as his ally.
I won't let you execute this man.
The restoration of the harbour will take a long time. Black blood clings and stinks like death itself.
You did we asked. You've earned this.
I saved these hostages from an underwater prison. No harm to the sea was intended.
Step out of the way, and hand over the master of the beast. Or Umberlee will swallow you whole.
Then you've made your choice. You supplicate to the ocean or you are sucked down, down, down.
There is nothing left for us here, sisters.
There you are! Conspirators with the Abomination. Do you know the harbour is sickened with blood so black the sea itself chokes?

EditorData.logicalname: Beastmaster is alive, never got quest from Waveservants

Text.Value: With the Bitch Queen's blessings, we take our leave.
So often the Wavemother pays the price for the sins of men.
I don't answer to you.
You. You were to administer Umberlee's justice! Instead you conspire with the Abomination? He who sickened the harbour with blood so black the sea itself chokes?
What?! Mate - you've got to be kidding.
Come quietly. The Sea Queen will judge you.
The bay is tainted with black blood. The Wavemother's citizens wither and choke.
Yes - the Iron Throne is gone because of me. It will taint your waters no longer.
You don't understand. He wasn't responsible for the destruction in the harbour.
Did you do this?
I surrrender, all right? You wouldn't hurt a harmless man, right? And you, thanks for nothing, prick.

EditorData.NodeContext: Last line is directed to the player.

Text.Value: Waveservants: Destroy them.
Gods! They're nuts. You have to help me.
But you killed the beast's master. You've earned this.
I was trying to save hostages from an underwater prison. But I failed. They're all dead.
Indeed. We all of us answer to the Sea herself, whether we know it or not.

Synopsis:
The waveservants confront you when they see you come out of  the submersible. The beastmaster might be dead or not at this point, and they would have found his corpse if he's dead as it would be in the basement.

They only come if you have spoken to them and they have given you the quest.

You can hand over the beastmaster or  refuse and fight the waveservants. If you hand him over, they will reward you after he's dead the same way they would if you report his death before going to the iron throne.

If the beastmaster is already dead, they confront you about all the destruction that resulted from the Iron Throne's explosions. Since the beastmaster is dead, they are willing to let you go if you tell them you were there for a good cause.
